text: Park Sun-young (born 17 February 1968) is a South Korean taekwondo athlete. She won the bronze medal at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the bantamweight event. At the Asian Taekwondo Championships she became Asian Champion in 1988 after winning the bronze medal in 1986. == References == == Other websites == * Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean taekwondo practitioners
